- Creates virtual DOM in memory
- Instead of manipulating the browser's DOM directly, React creates a virtual DOM in memory, where it does all the necessary manipulating, before     making the changes in the browser DOM.
- React only changes what needs to be changed


React render HTML
    - React renders HTML to the web page via a container, and a function called createRoot().
    - Typically, this container is a <div id="root"></div> element in the index.html file.

    CreateRoot() function
        - located in main.tsx in src (used to create root node)
        - The createRoot() function takes one argument, an HTML element.
        - Define the HTML element where a React component should be displayed.
    .render()
        - Defines whats in the element
    Root Node
        - The root node is the HTML element where you want to display the result.
        - It is like a container for content, managed by React.
        - It does NOT have to be a <div> element and it does NOT have to have the id='root':

